      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COTCHINELLIE (5) is flying having won three in a row at this circuit, the latest when overcoming a second row draw over a longer trip. The previous two wins were at this distance and he returns to the front row. Can deliver again. BELLISSIMO ACQUISTO NZ (1) overcame a second row draw when winning here three back and was brave last time, leading from wider and sticking on well to finish second and just a head from the winner. Has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw. STRIKEM NZ (7) is racing well having finished in the top-three in two of his three starts since winning here, one of those placings coming from this barrier. SIR RICHARD LEE (6) draws wider but must be respected after adding to his good form with a last-start win by a head at this circuit and distance.",
